jbt.model.core
Class ModelTask.Position

java.lang.Object
  jbt.model.core.ModelTask.Position
Enclosing class:
ModelTask
public static class ModelTask.Position
extends java.lang.Object

The position of a ModelTask in a behaviour tree. It contains the sequence of moves that must be performed to go from the root to the node itself. Each of the moves of the sequence represents what child of the current node must be selected. For instance, if the position represents the sequence of moves {1,4,0}, the node that it points to is the first child (0) of the fifth child (4) of the second child (1) of the root. En empty list of moves represents the root.
